University Hospital; Department of Neurology, Hospital General de Asturias, 
Oviedo) since 1995. DS had been diagnosed in all at birth, and all presented 
with the typical morphological changes associated with DS. We selected all cases 
(18) referred as adults with new onset of myoclonic jerks (MJ) and/or behavioral 
or cognitive deterioration (CD).

